quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
45,1,"Ha'. Mim."
45,2,"This Book is a revelation from the Most Mighty, the Most Wise. {1}",footnotes:1:In this brief introduction to the Surah
45,3,"Behold, for those who believe {1} there are (myriad) Signs in the heavens and the earth",footnotes:1:To begin the discourse like this after the introduction
45,4,"and in your own creation; and in the animals which He spreads out over the earth too there are Signs for those endowed with sure faith; {1}",footnotes:1:That is
45,5,"and in the succession of night and day, {1} and in the provision {2} that Allah sends down from the sky wherewith He gives life to the earth after it had been lifeless, {3} and in the change of the winds: {4} (in all these) there are Signs for people who use reason.",footnotes:1:Provision: Rainfall as becomes evident from the following sentence.For explanation
45,6,"These are Allah's Signs that We rehearse to you in Truth. In what kind of discourse after Allah and His Signs will they, then, believe? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
45,7,"Woe to every guilty impostor"
45,8,"who hears Allah's Signs being rehearsed to him, and yet persists in his pride, as though he had not heard it. {1} Announce to him, then, the tidings of a grievous chastisement.",footnotes:1:In other words
45,9,"Whenever he comes to know anything of Our Signs, he makes them an object of jest. {1} For such there awaits a humiliating chastisement.",footnotes:1:That is
45,10,"Hell is behind them. {1} Their worldly earnings shall not avail them, nor those whom they took as protectors instead of Allah. {2} An awesome chastisement lies in store for them.",footnotes:1:Here
45,11,"This (Qur'an) is the true guidance. Those who deny the Signs of their Lord shall suffer the torment of a woeful scourge."
45,12,"Allah it is Who has subjected the sea to you so that ships may sail upon it at His bidding {1} and you may seek of His Bounty {2} and give thanks to Him.",footnotes:1:For explanation
45,13,"He has subjected to you all that is in the heavens and the earth, {1} all being from Him. {2} Verily there are Signs in this for those who reflect. {3}",footnotes:1:(1) This gift and favor of Allah is not like the gift of the worldly kings
